snippet.textDisplay: Where is my problem with Porsche‚Äôs 911‚Äòs/Carrera, etc and this is coming from a Porsche owner. I had a 2020 Taycan 4S as my daily driver and now have a 2024 Taycan Turbo as my daily driver and absolutely love both cars.  But my issue with Porsche in general, especially the 911/Claire Carrera, etc. is that every year they come out with a ‚Äúnew model‚Äú and it looks exactly the same with very minor changes. If you look at it 2026 compared to like a 2017 there‚Äôs minimal differences. And if you look at basic 911 and a 911 S in a 911 turbo and a 911 turbo S there‚Äôs very minimal differences there either. I get it if you‚Äôre a big Porsche aficionado you will know all the differences in the headlights in the air intakes and the spoilers and where carbon fiber is etc. but for 99.9% of the people I can‚Äôt tell a difference between a 911 or a 911 turbo S when I see it on the streets.

snippet.textDisplay: I love how everybody says "Oh Porsche horsepower is worth more than American horsepower" when in reality that's not the case what's really going on is Porsches don't weigh much, are rear engine cars most of the time and they are liars about the car's power (which is a sin). If anybody wants an example of a time where Porsche horsepower was worth less than American horsepower it was when the 1020 horsepower Tesla Model S Plaid beat the 1034 horsepower Porsche Taycan Turbo GT. I know the Porsche fanboys who read that last sentence will probably say "Oh the Taycan Turbo GT with the weissach pack us quicker than a model S Plaid but keep in mind that if you do a slight tire modification you can get a model S Plaid to do the quarter mile almost half a second quicker. In case anybody is wondering according to the internet, the fastest time ever done by a Taycan turbo gt is 9.06 seconds and the fastest time ever done by a model S Plaid is 8.59 seconds. That's what I call a scam (on Porsche's part), because the model S Plaid will cost about 120 grand max where as the Taycan turbp gt's max price is 300 grand. If that's not highway robbery, I don't know what is.
